message.content: This question requires basic knowledge about magnetic properties of different materials. Magnets have the strongest effect on materials that are easily magnetized, such as metals. Wood, plastic, and cotton are not magnetic materials, so they would not be affected by a magnet. Titanium, on the other hand, is a paramagnetic material, which means it is weakly attracted to magnets. Therefore, a titanium beam would be the most affected by a magnet. Option (A) is incorrect because wood is not magnetic. Option (C) is incorrect because plastic is not magnetic. Option (D) is incorrect because cotton is not magnetic.
